Two stars.  Came here for a weekend brunch around 10:30 a.m. The place was pretty empty considering that it would be the prime time for brunch. We got seated right away.  Coffee au lait didn't have much of a coffee taste, just a lot of milk. Ice coffee was just bland. Nothing special.  Pancakes!! I saw three different types of pancakes - original, blueberry, and orange and walnut - and I chose the orange and walnut pancakes. It was $5 more than regular pancakes. Again, nothing special. Just pancakes with orange slices and very minimal amount of walnuts. The orange sauce was too tangy to go with the pancakes so I asked for maple syrup and butter.  My quest to find the perfect, fluffy, light pancakes would need to continue.  They forgot to serve us water.  There is a parking lot at the back of the building that is shared by 3 other stores. Very very limited parking. I street parked about 4 blocks away. Street parking are metered around this area, 4 quarters per hr except Sunday and holidays.

Ate from there twice. Both times I had an item missing (Rice from there Orange Chicken and a Pickle from my wrap). Normally, I wouldn't complain about a pickle but their 10$ Wraps/Sandwiches don't come with any sides, besides a pickle and coleslaw. So, I purchased a side of fries ($5.50) and it was embarrassingly empty. Don't be cheap when it comes to the fries, it's lame. The food tastes good but the value isn't there. If you go there I recommend to do carry out, so you can check that they got everything in the bag and you can scold them about the lack of fries for me.

Came here on a Sunday and the place was bustling. Sat outside to enjoy the good weather and the staff basically forgot about us. Food took forever and was subpar! I ordered two eggs any style (sunnyside up) and was not asked how I wanted them done, plus the "homefries" they came with were overdone and slightly bland. My friend had their tomato-mozzarella sandwich, which he rated a 3.5/10. The service was nonexistent; no one came to check up on us during our meal. When a server finally did show up, he already had the bill (what if we were going to order dessert or coffee???). Came here on the recommendation of a friend but I will not be back.

And, to get extra coffee, she was so busy and I had wait for long time to grab her attention. I wish the waitress was more caring and attentive. Very cute cafe in Fort Lee. Service is nice and attentive. We have been here for brunch several times and there are several good options, including various benedicts and omelettes plus the lunch menu (which has good panini options). The cafe is kids-friendly, we usually get our two kids two or three sides and that's enough for them. I highly recommend the orange juice and the smoothies, they're big and delicious.

James and his wife make the experience at Eggty 8 Cafe a special place to dine. Whether breakfast, lunch or dinner, you will be taken care of with the kind of hospitality you don't often see any more. The prices and the food are wonderful. An amazing place for lunch or brunch as well as dinner.
